\subsection{Generalised rewrite-bridge \texorpdfstring{$\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$}{} for HModule\texttt{'} (iter-052)}

Iter-051 lands $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i))$ on the lattice supremum. The iter-054+ producer for $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ on an affine open $U$ instead needs $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$ on the open $U$ itself; it picks a basic-open cover $\mathcal U$ of $U$ (with $\bigsqcup\mathcal U = U$ by construction) and rewrites via the equality. Iter-052 factors this rewrite into a thin theorem (mirroring iter-049's $h\,\rebind\,\mathtt{this}$ factoring at universe $u+1$ for $\HModule$), enabling the iter-054+ producer to use cleaner instance-driven synthesis.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Generalised rewrite-bridge HModule\texttt{'} consumer, abstract sheaf form, iter-052]
  \label{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.subsingleton_HModule'_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $F$ a sheaf of $\ModuleCat\,k$, $\mathcal U : \iota \to \Opens\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$, and $U : \Opens\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$ an arbitrary open. Assume $\HasExt_u$ on the sheaf category (single-universe). Under $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$, $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$, an equality hypothesis $h : \bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i = U$, and $n \geq 1$, the type $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U$ is a subsingleton.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
\leanok
  Direct rewrite application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}: the iter-051 consumer gives $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i))$, and substituting $\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i = U$ via $h \rebind \mathtt{this}$ yields the desired $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,U)$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-052 pass) confirms the body $\mathtt{haveI := subsingleton\_HModule}'\_\mathtt{supr\_of\_hasCechToHModuleIso}\,(F := F)\,(\mathcal U := \mathcal U)\,n\,h_n;\;\mathtt{exact}\,h \rebind \mathtt{this}$ typechecks end-to-end with kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
